article.headline: Bradley 69, Bowling Green 56
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. (AP) -- Phillip Gilbert scored 23 points as Bradley beat Bowling Green 69-56 Saturday. James Gillingham scored 17 points and Marcellus Sommerville added 15 for Bradley (4-1). Point gouard Marcello Robinson pulled down seven rebounds and had eight assists -- both team highs for Bradley. The Braves took a 36-26 lead at the half and then outscored Bowling Green by three points in the second half. Bowling Green (2-1) was led by Kevin Netter with 17 points. Ronald Lewis and Steven Wright each scored 12. Lewis led Bowling Green with seven rebounds.
